author: Nikki Schwab
title: DNC Chair candidate tells his fellow Dems to 'grow up' | Daily Mail Online
text: show ad DNC Chair candidate Raymond Buckley tells his fellow Democrats to 'grow up!' Democratic National Committee chair candidate Raymond Buckley panned the party for running holier-than-thou ads against Republican Donald Trump Buckley, the New Hampshire chair, said working class voters didn't care Trump was an 'insult dog,' because they were worrying about their 'damn paycheck' He said the party failed in 2016 because it had no message for anyone related to him - instead telling voters to be offended by Trump Published: 23:42 GMT, 12 February 2017 | Updated: 00:32 GMT, 13 February 2017 30 shares
